# ---- Build artifacts (ESP32 / Arduino) ----
build/
*.bin
*.elf
*.hex

# ---- Python ----
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# ---- Node / web ----
node_modules/

# ---- Logs ----
*.log

# ---- OS ----
.DS_Store

# Rust build artifacts
target/
**/target/
*.rs.bk

# WiFi credentials / secrets — never commit (repo is public)
secrets.rs
**/secrets.rs
*secrets.h
wifi_secrets.*

# Per-board config (issue #19) — identity/config (NODE_ID, DEFAULT_APP), NOT
# credentials. Git-ignored so a per-board build dirties no tracked file (clean
# version stamp). The tracked template is board.rs.example (cp it on a fresh clone).
board.rs
**/board.rs

# #147 hardening: also ignore BACKUP / VARIANT siblings of the secret files — a loose
# `secrets.rs.pre142.bak` (real creds, NOT matched by `**/secrets.rs`) nearly rode a
# commit, and the repo is PUBLIC. The `.example` TEMPLATES must stay TRACKED, so they
# are re-included via explicit negation (order matters: exclude then negate).
**/secrets.rs.*
!**/secrets.rs.example
**/board.rs.*
!**/board.rs.example
# Editor/tooling backups under the firmware crate src (belt-and-suspenders).
rust/clock/src/*.bak
rust/clock/src/**/*.bak

# OTA publish infra config (issue #6) — real host/broker/addon values for
# tools/ota_publish.sh. Git-ignored (repo is public); the tracked template is
# tools/ota_publish.env.example (cp it → tools/ota_publish.env, edit). No password here.
tools/ota_publish.env

# brainstorm visual-companion sessions (local mockups)
.superpowers/

# #152 web emulator build artifacts
rust/web-emu/target/
web/emulator/*.wasm
# #152: the generated (base64-wasm-inlined) page is a build artifact — regenerate via
# build.sh; source of truth is index.template.html + build.sh (no blob churn in git).
web/emulator/index.html
web/emulator/dist/
